DMASC_51.Description: Sum of scores of items 42, 45, 48, and 49. | Calculation = [DMASC_42]+[DMASC_45]+[DMASC_48]+[DMASC_49]

DMASC_52.Description: Identifies random or inconsistent responses by using summed difference scores on items that are expected to be highly intercorrelated: absolute value(question 2 - question 11) + absolute value(question 3- question 10) + absolute value(question 8 – question 15) + absolute value(question 12 - question 18) + absolute value(question 13 – question 36) + absolute value(question 14 – question 33) + absolute value(question 16 – question 22) + absolute value(question 30 – question 34). An Inconsistency Index of 12 or greater for 8-11 year olds, and 10 or greater for 12-19 year olds may indicate some inconsistency to the responses and results should be interpreted with caution. Low scores indicate valid responding. | Calculation = abs_f([DMASC_02]-[DMASC_11])+ abs_f([DMASC_03]-[DMASC_10])+ abs_f([DMASC_08]-[DMASC_15])+ abs_f([DMASC_12]-[DMASC_18])+abs_f([DMASC_13]-[DMASC_36])+abs_f([DMASC_14]-[DMASC_33])+abs_f([DMASC_16]-[DMASC_22])+ abs_f([DMASC_30]-[DMASC_34])
